text:
enough is enough🔥🔥🔥
stop the hate❗️
。
how many times did you get upset reading the news last week?
how many times did you witness hatred?
how many times did you react?
。
it is not about blaming but about reflecting on our past. have you done enough to stop the hatred?
have we done enough to guarantee safe future for our children?
。
the answer is no.
so let’s act now❗️
past is in the past.
future is in the future.
the only thing that we have the full power over is the present moment.
so start ｌｏｖｉｎｇ  now!💗
it is never too late🙏🕊✨
。
i was bullied at school as a child because of my hair colour. i was called names i wouldn’t dare to repeat. one of the nicer ones was ‘carrion’ because i was not only ginger but also very pale... like a dead body...
my bullies were mostly boys... taught at home, that they can disrespect a girl like that and it is ok. 。
today i know that they did it because of the lack of love from their parents. was i a saint? for sure not. aggression causes aggression and i tried to protect myself by being mean at times. but unfortunately most of that anger got internalized and i punished myself the most. i suffered from depression for years.
。
but through regular practice of sport, yoga asana and meditation i healed my suffering💗🧘‍♀️🕊
i developed a deep sense of self love and i forgave my bullies. forgiveness is the key to liberating oneself from the chains of the past.
。
i am sorry for all the evil i might have caused. i am sorry for the suffering of my bullies. i wish them all the best for the future and i hope that they will love their kids and teach them the language of love, not hatred❤️
。
as buddha said:
‘hatred does not cease by hatred, but only by love; this is the eternal rule.‘
。
so forgive and love.
start now💗🙏🕊
。
。
。
i got inspired by my very favorite fitness star @chodakowskaewa who joined a movement against the violence towards women. many of us were victims without knowing it! educate. speak up. thank you ewa🙏🕊✨
。
#stopprzemocy #misjachoda #ewachodakowska #stopthehate #stopbullying #enoughisenough #timeisup #metoo #metoomovement #bullying #deppression #orangetheworld #trauma #love #yoga #meditation #sport #forgiveness

text:
frauen*, die feministinnen sind, sind nicht alle am rande der gesellschaft und anders als die anderen. du kannst feministin sein und dich schminken, oder sexarbeiterin sein, oder du kannst zuhause bleiben und dich um deine kinder kümmern, während dein partner das geld verdient, oder alles zusammen. feminismus will das nicht beenden, sondern nur nicht mehr als notwendigkeit darstellen. 
alle menschen sollten die gleichen rechte besitzen, ob mann oder frau, ob poc (person of color) oder weiß, ob dick oder dünn, egal welcher herkunft oder sexueller orientierung: intersectional feminism eben.
frauen sollen nicht mehr rechte haben als männer oder ihnen gesellschaftlich überlegen sein, sondern mit ihnen auf einer stufe stehen. männer genießen momentan privilegien gegenüber dem weiblichen geschlecht (welche privilegien, willst du wissen? dann lies meinen beitrag dazu, den ich vor kurzem hochgeladen habe). feministen/-innen wollen gleichberechtigung. du kannst tun und lassen was immer du willst, solange es niemandem schadet. feminismus ist also keine extreme position, sondern eine, die maßgebend für ein gesundes miteinander auf unserer erde sein sollte.

text:
🚨warning: triggering and long post! 🌺🌸🌻
these are the heaviest words. several years ago all i could do was lay on the floor. the shame of these words by people i respected and thought cared for me were surprising. the strange thing about shame is that you internalize it and count it as truth. slowly the support from family, friends, my faith community, and amazing nonprofits lightened the burden. the more i was heard and provided with empathy-even telling me to stop blaming myself- the burden became bearable. 🎒👜💼
i have shared my story with several people over the years but never to strangers or in public. this weekend that changed. i reflected on why i have a passion for empowering women and decided to carry a sign with the heaviest words-more than can fit on a poster. thanks amy for the artistic presentation! i carried this sign and it again felt too heavy. slowly i saw too many at the womxn’s march in denver carrying similar words. i held my sign a little higher for us. then gradually numerous people came up to me providing support with hugs and words of encouragement. i held my sign with strength because we have more power than those words. 🙍🏿‍♀️🙍🏼‍♀️🙍🏽‍♀️🙍🏻‍♀️🙍🏾‍♀️
for those of you who doubt survivors and even doubt me, i understand. i doubted survivors and even myself. after living my story and the shock of others reactions i had to deconstruct some of my beliefs about the world. i haven’t figured it out but it’s a process. the initial trauma happened in one night but the hardest part was the salt being poured into the wound by trusted people’s words. ❤️💜🧡💛💚💙
i share my story to help others understand, increase empathy, and hopefully support others through listening, volunteering, and giving to organizations. it has taken time and support from countless people to clean out the wound and lighten the burden. if you or someone else is struggling with sexual assault or abuse please reach out to the resources in your community. but most importantly believe and support survivors! 🔑⚖️💰⌛️
https://www.rainn.org/
https://www.ywca.org/
http://savacenter.org/

##womxnsmarch #imarchbecause #metoo #mystory #supportsurvivors  #stopvictimblaming

text:
#movement 
yesterday i attended the rev. dr. mlk, jr. commemorative ceremony at duke chapel. the keynote was given by tarana burke, founder of the me too movement. she spoke of how words matter and though her words were a tribute to mlk, jr., the message behind the words was to honor the women of color that surrounded and supported him. often times these women were the unsung heroes of the civil rights movement. 
the women pictured are some of those women. if you aren’t familiar with these faces or names, i invite you to expand what you already know. honor the legacy of what they and so many others, including mlk, jr., stood for. we must ask ourselves, “what can we do to create an equitable and just world.... where possibility is fueled by love?” left to right, top and bottom. 
joanne robinson, a professor of english, was an outspoken critic of the treatment of african- americans on public transportation.  she created the women’s political council, which laid the groundwork for the montgomery bus boycott, sparked by rosa park’s arrest. 
dr. dorothy cotton was the highest-ranking female in the southern christian leadership conference ( sclc). determined to confront the patriarchy within the movement, she was one of the women who courageously spoke to the existing sexism in the movement. 
ella baker, viewed by some as the most influential woman in the civil rights movement, that birthed the organization and set its agenda, had pivotal roles in the national naacp and the student nonviolent coordinating committee (sncc). diane nash, was one of the major organizers of the selma to montgomery voting rights marches in 1965 and helped orchestrate the campaign to integrate lunch counters in nashville in 1960.

pauli murray, the gender non-conforming activist and legal scholar who coined the term "jane crow" for the sex discrimination black women faced. her book states’ laws on race and color has been referred to as the “bible” of brown v. board of education, the 1954 supreme court ruling which declared separate public schools for black and white students unconstitutional. #mlkjr #liberation #justice #love #metoo #thetimeisalwaysrighttodowhatisright #blacklivesmatter

text:
in honor of martin luther king junior, here are some of his most poignant words:
.
“darkness cannot drive out darkness; only light can do that. hate cannot drive out hate; only love can do that.”
.
“injustice anywhere is a threat to justice everywhere.”
.
“our lives begin to end the day we become silent about things that matter.”
.
“the time is always right to do what is right.”
.
advocating for what we believe in is speaking from the soul. this weekend, i spoke for i believe to be true at the women’s march.  i marched with my fellow soul sisters, women, and men from all walks of life. ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🖤 and i walked as an example to teach my son. —-
standing for something with conviction is so important. to see and feel how powerful it is when a group of individuals come together to create change, is a an amazing experience. what can stand for to set your soul on fire? 🔥 .
.
.
.
.

text:
martin luther king has always been a big influence in my life, after learning about him as a young girl, studying him in my college civil rights classes and later in life having one of my essays bought & included in his daughter yolanda king's book, who i had the pleasure of meeting when she invited me to read my essay at her book launch and be a participating author at the book signing held @ the martin luther king library in san jose, ca. his words of hope, equality & perseverence still serve as a driving force within me, affecting every decision i make.
gutsee ink has always represented equality, self acceptance & strength...of knowing that being who you are is always good unuf. our signature line brave unuf to be me is a reminder to the world that we believe in our dreams, in our decisions & in ourselves and we are not looking for anyone's approval. 
happy martin luther king day.

text:
i'm often asked why? why do i talk about my kidnapping & rape? why do i march? why do i protest? 
i speak up for several reasons. 
we need to have those difficult discussions, the ones that make us cringe and want to shove our fingers in our ears and say.."lalala not listening!". the ones that compel action and change. 
i cannot complain about my circumstances if i am not willing to do something to change them. i cannot complain about the world around me if i am not willing to volunteer my time and make a difference. i'm not perfect, none of us are.  however, i do my best to be involved in my community, not just saying things need to change, but doing the things that lead to change. 
desmond tutu was quoted in saying "if you are neutral in situations of injustice, you have chosen the side of the oppressor. if an elephant has its foot on the tail of a mouse and you say that you are neutral, the mouse will not appreciate your neutrality." start small. decide what is important to you and find an organization in your community that is in line with your values. go volunteer. go give. go make a change.

...
...

text:
mlk monday motivation. a weekend of friendship, solidarity, movement, and brilliance. here is to the work and the fight for freedom. thanks @chasinggarza for all of your work and love. on behalf of @aapiwomenlead and as a vietnamese woman born in oakland, i share a quote from dr. mlk’s famous speech against the vietnam war or war in vietnam,
***
“they must see americans as strange liberators. the vietnamese people proclaimed their own independence in 1954 -- in 1945 rather -- after a combined french and japanese occupation and before the communist revolution in china...even though they quoted the american declaration of independence in their own document of freedom, we refused to recognize them. instead, we decided to support france in its reconquest of her former colony. our government felt then that the vietnamese people were not ready for independence, and we again fell victim to the deadly western arrogance that has poisoned the international atmosphere for so long... these are revolutionary times. all over the globe men are revolting against old systems of exploitation and oppression, and out of the wounds of a frail world, new systems of justice and equality are being born. the shirtless and barefoot people of the land are rising up as never before. "the people who sat in darkness have seen a great light." we in the west must support these revolutions.”
.
and be them. we live this fight everywhere - domestically and internationally - and everyday. for freedom. in solidarity. .
.
#martinlutherkingjr #mlkday #womenempowerment #womensmarchoakland #womenswave #womensmarch #womenofcolor #aapiwomenlead #insolidarity #vietnamese #aapi #asianactivism #metoo #feminist

text:
this picture means everything. i saw so many men at the women’s march in los angeles on saturday. proud men. men with women, young boys, men wearing pink hats and men carrying signs. don’t tell me that men aren’t ready for the #metoo movement. men are ready. and some of these men are paving the way. and that’s what we need—imperfect love but love that is willing to see the sacrifices women make and honor them.❤️
.
p.s. @kamalaharris just announced her candidacy for president. 😍
.
.

text:
last night i had the pleasure of sharing the stage with an awesome group of women at the 2019 song slam festival in nyc by @sparksandwirycries. not only was i able to create with my very first childhood friend for the #metoo path to healing series but also collaborated with a black composer and black opera singer to birth nobody knows. a million thanks to @kikislacksoprano for pouring yourself into my words and giving back fiyah!! #northphillyproud .
.
.
.
nobody knows

nobody knows black girl magic acts as cover for the hurt and sadness left by unwanted advances 
nobody knows

when we’re taken advantage of

nobody knows

innocence gone and broken

too many brown girls share the same secret

touches forced entry

nobody knows

our anger masks the empty space where strong men turned savage mismanaged masculinity

nobody knows

family friends clothed wolves and snakes fake love and camouflaged tendencies

nobody knows about

attacks you know occurred but pretend that it didn’t no witness to this crime a victim 
nobody knows

shame and open wounds from overly suggestive words aggressive action i didn’t ask for

responsible for his attraction i didn’t say yes to

nobody knows

no media coverage or under cover report

on the unsolicited taking of precious jewels 
nobody knows that 
sometimes women steal from us too

we got competing views because we matter more than your desire for us 
scarred but we survive and thrive because
we refuse to be what happened to us raising our voices refusing to let the predators win

their sin is not ours to carry

we stand up for our right to say no and mean it

despite the length of my skirt cleavage in my shirt or liquor in my blood

my body is still mine, fine without his validation 
me too

come from under the white shadow we dare to speak out and say

i stand with you in your trauma, making a way out of nothing, out of suffering and insert joy and rise up me too centered to re enter myself and the world a new bruised maybe but never defeated even with this thing that happened to me and you and her our gifts still need and deserve love and wonder and sunshine and honor the royalty in us
too strong 
loud
black 
brown 
proud woman.

text:
la curiosidad mató al 😿(aunque murió más sabio 😼) no me sigas por algo malo, que el/la que siembra recoge 💞 tampoco lo hagas si eres menor.

si pinchas en este enlace y tiras hacia abajo un poquito, verás cómo me presenta la editorial mito: https://mitoeditorial.blogspot.com/p/autor-invitado.html 👋😹👍🐩💫
puedes leer artículos míos en diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa) y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🦄💂 mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: 
my novels arrive everywhere from

http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu

pincha el enlace en mi perfil.
verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores de 18 años.

you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults. 😘 
todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com

puedes seguirme también en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud (otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)

text:
“this photo was taken on halloween when i was in high school in new york city,” says darci, 20, now a student at vassar. “the day before, the school had made an announcement over the loudspeakers: ‘girls, no inappropriate costumes will be tolerated. boys, no masks.” in other words: ‘girls, don’t wear slutty costumes. and boys, um, well, how can we make this fair… don’t be too scary.’ so all the girls were #dresscoded by the school administration before we even had put on our costumes. on halloween a group of boys arrived in matching referee uniforms with whistles and badges, calling themselves the ‘thot patrol.’ (‘thot’ stands for ‘that ho over there.’) they would blow their whistles and hoot any girl they thought looked ‘thotty.’ i complained to my english teacher, a feminist ally, who brought me to the principal. but all that happened was that they were told to remove their thot patrol badges or shirts. none of them actually did though.” @dsiegz

text: on #mlkday we celebrate a giant. he stood when others chose to sit on their hands. he didn’t believe in fists. he was nonviolent in the way of ghandi, even when violence and war threatened his home, family and friends. most of us know of his dream of a better nation for all of our children. a great nation is without walls, borders and limitations. in a great nation, none of our children will ever sleep in a cage. no child is illegal, even when mom and pops have an unresolved immigration status. a great nation doesn’t have a zimmerman on its streets. in great nations black and brown men aren’t caged for decades for nonviolent offenses. doctor king believed we should all be judged by the  content of our characters... today our government has been #shutdown for 31 days - the longest #governmentshutdown in american history. thousands of workers are steadying against the blow of a sudden end to income. america remains in a forever war in the middle east. we are blighted by a ban against muslims from “marked” nations. america is an occupying force and global menace... #shitholecountries is a thing now. our nation is at its lowest point since people were hosed in the streets for the sake of social justice. dr. king walked 54 miles from selma to montgomery in protest. what would king say about america today? the election of president obama holds great promise. many of us are willing to roll up our sleeves and build a civic and truly representative society and government. enough of us are willing to practice our “preach” so that life, liberty and the pursuit of happiness aren’t beyond our babies. we all have good reasons to want a better future. history will record many movements that shifted the way we live, work, love, play and engage.  king walked 54 miles so you and i can take another step. - samaad barnes, pure love bakery #withlove #loveis #openletter #purelovebakery #mybrotherskeeper #beanpies #muslimsinamerica #blacklivesmatters #immigrationreform #metoo #prisonreform #socialjustice #equalpayforwomen #ilovenj #njeats #therecipeforlove #greatsacrifices #goodmorning #navybeanpiesrus

text:
today is martin luther king jr day. quick gab about why this is important. mlk jr is the pioneer and leader of the nonviolent civil rights movement. he organized these protests for freedom, peace and equality founded on his christian beliefs. he was a baptist minister and winner of the nobel peace prize in 1964, the youngest person to ever receive this honor. his iconic speech "i have a dream", was given during the march on washington in 1963 and he got to see the civil rights act and the voting rights act passed before his assassination in 1968. 
mlk jr. is solely responsible for the beginning of civil rights. today there is a lot of internet and media chatter about things that are deemed "civil rights"; issues and topics such as toxic masculinity, feminism, #metoo, black lives matter, all just to name a few. the country has begun the same rumblings echoed in our history just 56 years ago; civil unrest and discord. while musing on this today, mlk jr would have wanted his continued pursuit for civil rights to be reflective of his speech that day in washington. "i have a dream today....with this faith we will be able to transform the jangling discords of our nation into a beautiful symphony of brotherhood". i implore of you all in your heated debates and political debacles that ensue, to think of mlk jr. find your commonality and perhaps this country will be able to find itself, again. 
#mlk #lovequotes #civilityandunrest #historymemes

text:
how do we achieve happiness? society teaches us to pursue happiness in materialistic and idealistic ways. be successful at work. have many friends (documented online). buy a house. create a family. behave in a gender-specific manner. strive for the body you see in magazines. try that food fad. wear the current fashion trend. read the newest books and watch the biggest movies. these things can bring joy to some of us, but what happens when we cannot afford the latest technology, or we cheat on our diet, or we make a mistake at work: are we unhappy? society tells us to place social media presence above relationships, and popularity above love. it says we should be defined by the value of our material possessions rather than our principles, actions and behaviours. it tells us that how we appear to others is more important than how we know ourselves. societal paradigms are prioritised over truer sources of satisfaction and fulfilment: our own individual criteria for happiness. learn to understand yourself then your idea of happiness will morph accordingly. start by recognising your core values - those principles that you judge to be most important - and aim to abide by them. happiness has its peaks and troughs but, by putting yourself at its centre, you can continue the cycle of highs to lows to highs and experience it in its many forms. ~copingdiary ~
~

text: "a man known to my family and a lot of my friends, got really close to me, groomed me and then raped me. he was a very angry soul and i was terrified of him and what he was capable of doing. so this post was about not letting his manipulation and his abuse (of all kinds) get to me and letting myself become consumed in anxiety and fear, and letting the words he would say over my life become me, and just taking my control back, because no one else has the right over my life and what happens with it. my heart hurts so much for everything that i went through with him and i needed to find a way to get what i’m feeling outside of my body to help myself to heal with my power in my control. he raped me on more than one occasion; the first was my virginity, although he promised he wouldn’t... but he did and that was the first moment my life turned upside down and he began to control me. he was 21 years older than me and i am now 22."

vi känner alla någon. offer och gärningsperson.

text:
рождение бабочки🦋
⠀
куколка долгие дни пребывает в абсолютной неподвижности, и все это время в ней бурно протекают важные жизненные процессы🐛 ⠀
покровы куколки становятся прозрачными, и уже можно предугадать краски и формы бабочки. вот-вот из куколки наружу выйдет великолепная красавица. а когда это произойдет, зависит от температуры воздуха и продолжительности дня. ⠀
покровы куколки рвутся по швам — на голове, на спине и вокруг усиков. а вот вилохвост даже выделяет особое вещество, благодаря которому кокон сам раскрывается, когда бабочке придет пора выйти из куколки. ⠀
бабочка засасывает воздух, раздувается, становится больше и постепенно, миллиметр за миллиметром, выходит наружу. сначала появляются голова и грудь. затем бабочка вытаскивает брюшко.
⠀
крылья ее еще влажные и висят пустыми кожистыми «мешочками». вскоре «мешочки» расправляются в изящные крылья. но прежде чем бабочка взлетит, они должны еще несколько часов посушиться, чтобы обрести жесткость. ⠀
от куколки остается лишь сброшенная шкурка и кучка экскрементов, продуктов выделения, накопившихся за период существования куколки.
⠀
🔴и весь этот процесс вы можете увидеть своими глазами, заказав у нас мини-ферму для разведения бабочек. в ней есть все, от куколок до инструкции☝️

text:
it has been one year since i was sexually assaulted. it wasn’t by some stranger in the club who slipped a pill in my drink, it wasn’t whilst i was running late at night.
it wasn’t any of the scenarios i had been warned about. it was someone who was meant to protect me, someone who drove me home so i wouldn’t have to get the train in the dark, someone who always made sure my phone had battery. but it was also someone who threatened to kill themselves when i wanted time away from them. someone who went through my phone at every chance they got. someone who cried in a nightclub because someone else tried to dance with me, someone who hurt me and manipulated me into doing things i didn’t want to. i guess the point of this post is to be aware. “in the year ending march 2018, an estimated 2.0 million adults experienced domestic abuse in the last year (1.3 million women, 695,000 men).” (office for national statistics). domestic abuse isn’t just sexual assault and physical abuse. it’s also emotional abuse, does your partner belittle you and insult you. financial abuse, do they refuse to let you have a job or are actively unhappy that you are earning your own money. psychological abuse, do they do something then claim you are lying? do they hurt themselves and blame it on you. if you think you or a friend is in an abusive relationship there is always help and support. it doesn’t have to be like this. 
https://www.nhs.uk/live-well/healthy-body/getting-help-for-domestic-violence/

the artist commissioned for the 'mother and child' commemorative artwork, is wiltshire based @rebeccahawkinssculpture . she creates art which explores the strength and courage of women in situations, where they are culturally or socially stigmatised.

talking at the lai dai han event last week, she said; "i listened to their testimonials, i heard their pain, anger, disbelief, and despair at what life had thrown at them. i thought 'how on earth can i talk for these women, and their children, when i haven't walked in their shoes."
.
.
.
.

text:
if you know me on a more personal level, you are likely aware that i am a trauma survivor. but it didn’t end there...i survived all the nights i unfortunately drank too much alcohol because i was trying to escape from my painful past. i have also survived many sleepless nights, flashbacks, anxiety attacks, nonexistent self-worth, low self-esteem, and bouts of depression. i have never been a super religious person but i always assumed there was a purpose for my pain. regardless of how angry i was with god at times, i prayed to be shown my purpose over and over...which brings me to today. i am close to being a licensed mental health counselor and every day i help people struggling with trauma, anxiety, depression, addiction, low self-esteem, etc. if i can save even one life, it has given my pain a purpose! i have a feeling i’ll help save many lives though. 💚

text:
this is so true and getting sober from alcohol is what allowed me stop wasting so much of my time on people, places and things that were creating illness and distraction. 
alcohol doesn't only impact the night you were drinking but so many thoughts leading up to the drinking, the anxiety and depression that comes after drinking and managing the hangover.  the entire process of drinking is a waste if time when you really think about it and give yourself the experience of sobriety. you quickly see it's not even providing the connection between friends and family members that people think it does, it's actually inhibiting true connection, wastes money and leaves us unsatisfied and still seeking authentic connection. 
sobriety provides a simplified life focused on what's really important 💓

text:
i was a little sad to have missed the women’s march in the usa, but now i’m really happy i was here for this: ⁣
⁣
#todxssomosmartha⁣
⁣
there was a women’s march here in quito yesterday, and it was an incredible protest event. the impetus for this mass resistance to patriarchy is incredibly sad, though: last sunday, on january 13th, a woman named martha was brutally raped by three men she thought were friends in a bar. the men are in custody, while martha is in critical condition in the hospital. ⁣
⁣
this, as only an example of gendered violence that is all to common around the world, sparked incredible outrage. thousands of people turned out for the protest, to support equal rights for women, an end to sexual violence, and to express outrage at the treatment of rape and misogyny in our culture. ⁣
⁣
i feel incredibly blessed to be here to witness this spark in the fires of feminist revolution so far from home, and to have been able to lend my voice, feeble though it may be, to the chorus demanding justice and equality. ⁣
⁣
#todassomosmartha #todossomosmartha #justiciaparamartha #niunamas #niunamás #vivasnosqueremos #quito #ecuador #womensmarch #protest #feminist #revolution #feministrevolution #metoo

text: the narrator of milkman is an eighteen year old girl, coming of age in the troubled times of the 70’s, in what is believed, although never specified as burns’ ireland. she has what she refers to as her “maybe boyfriend”, because any further commitment to “boyfriend “ status makes the pair off balance. then the milkman who is not a milkman, begins (what we now would easily call) stalking her. given that he never touches her, and almost never even looks her in the eye, she wonders has he actually done anything to her? is there really anything to report? they only crossed paths twice, and she has become the subject of the gossip mill of the town, especially as far as her mother and third brother-in-law are concerned. it was not an easy time for women back then. people were so set in their ways, the only color possible for the sky was blue, light blue or dark blue. but clearly, according to the gorgeous book cover, the sky could even be pink or purple! although i found it challenging to read, (burns’ unique writing style, and the very long paragraphs and chapters give you very few breaks), but in the end, it is well worth it. winner of the 2018 man booker prize. #annaburns #milkman #manbookerprize #manbooker2018 #ireland #chips #middlesister #readingwhilewalking #whitevan #chef #metoo
name: Cheryl Sokoloff

text_retweet:
overall, the police response was pretty reasonable — a protest like this in the states would likely have ended in tear gas and other violence, i think. when the crowd moved to take a new street while marching, generally the police just moved to direct traffic. ⁣
⁣
the only tense moments were right near the beginning — when the first street was occupied, and everyone sat down, and then when the crowd took the other side of the street, a bit later. there were a few people that started that, which the police attempted to forcibly remove from the street: in response, the crowd rushed in to support their comrades, and the police quickly realized they were vastly outnumbered and retreated to redirect traffic around the protest. ⁣
⁣
i’ll try to repost some footage of that later: it was pretty dramatic, and a wonderful example of strength in unity against power. ⁣
⁣
notice in that first picture the two women cops in the back laughing, while all the men look super serious. this may have been when the crowd was chanting about putting rapists’ dicks in blenders. ⁣
⁣

text:
a california girl at heart—everything in me (physically and mentally) rejects the winter. there’s nothing that rejuvenates me more than being outdoors, feeling the ground beneath my bare feet, and taking in the sights and sounds of god’s beauty...hence my barefoot wedding at a nature preserve 🙋🏽‍♀️.
.
so...in honor of the 3° temperature outside, here’s a little throwback to a heart-opening stretch & flow session on my old patio. simple practices like these, where i can honor my body and indulge in the things i value (nature)—these practices make me feel most at home within myself. what are those practices for you?
.

outfit: pants @lululemon , bra @beyondyoga , top @urbanoutfitters

text:
we are creating a public art as a reminder of the plight of the lai dai han. 
the lai dai han 'mother and child' is based on the concept of the strangler fig tree, which is common in vietnam. the mother represents one of the vietnam war's many victims of sexual assault at the hands of south korean soldiers. the child represents one of the lai dai han, born as a result of these acts.
the strangler fig is a parasitic plant which takes over a host tree; it will be used as a metaphor, to resonate with the way these women's lives, minds, futures & emotions have been suppressed by what happened to them.
artist: @rebeccahawkinssculpture .

text:
valentina nappi contro vittorio sgarbi. il primo scontro fondamentale di questo 2019. dal lato della nappi abbiamo una visione pasoliniana sicché tutto è politica, ogni termine può assumere un significato politico proprio come per pasolini era il cannibalismo nella sua ultima intervista. la forma non può essere limitata all'identità e questo si riflette anche nella quotidianità. in tal modo anche una pornostar può parlare di politica in virtù del caos delle forme. non sembra dello stesso avviso vittorio sgarbi che con veemenza assume una posizione identitaria che valorizza le regole che predeterminano i requisiti formali. lo sgarbi infatti localizza l'interconnessione forma sostanza nei suoi requisiti minimi che per questo non permettono divagazioni. è già nella storia la frase dello sgarbi "l'unica conoscenza che ha è di un infinito universo di cazzi". il risultato dello scontro rappresenta in realtà una scissione nel pensiero di spinoza. se finora abbiamo sentito parlare di sinistra e destra hegeliana, da oggi in poi si potrà anche parlare di sinistra e destra spinoziana grazie ai protagonisti di questo scontro che sono ipso iure divenuti rappresentanti delle due opposite correnti.

#tv #valentinanappi #vittoriosgarbi #porno #filosofia #brazzers #spinoza #trash #infinity #salvini #metoo #m5s #lega

text:
da brat has weighed in on the whole r. kelly saga.

the chicago rapper was interviewed by tmz at the trumpet awards in atlanta on saturday (jan. 19), and the current radio host had an interesting take when asked about the fallout from the whole surviving r. kelly docuseries. the topic is a difficult one to touch on for da brat, as she knows the singer more than most. “that’s s a rough one,” she responded when asked her take. “i do think he needs help. i love him. i grew up with him. he’s kind of like family.” kelly and brat went to the same high school and were taught by the same music teacher. she admits she’s never seen anything out of order with the singer. but she also questions why a parent would let their child be around an accused pedophile. “i’ve never seen him do anything bad, but i don’t believe these people are lying,” brat added. “but at the same time, where is the parents? i think he needs help, for sure. i love him. i hope he don’t get mad at me. and i think the parents need to take responsibility. where is your 14-year-old child? why are you there? there’s something wrong with that.” she, however, will not be participating in the mute r. kelly movement. “i can’t stop listening to the music,” she said.

see what da brat has to say about the r. kelly situation in the full story at www.itskenbarbie.com or swipe do you agree with her? #dabrat #brat #femalerapper #femalerappers #sosobrat #rkelly #robertkelly #survivingrkelly #muterkelly #lifetimetv #trappedinthecloset #metoo #entertainment #entertainmentnews #entertainmentblog #gossip

while observing and honoring mlk remember he was fighting for equality.  the second amendment is for everyone regardless of race, sex, color, or religion.

dr. king was denied a concealed carry permit for self defense by the state of alabama back in 1956. he was a peaceful man but understood the human right to defend himself as he saw fit. 
in the 1960’s the naacp brought in the nra to train their members to defend themselves from the kkk in north carolina. 
gun rights are civil rights!

text:
but wylie wasn’t just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: “information operations”, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us military’s doctrine of the “five-dimensional battle space”. his brief ranged across the scl group – the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it.
.
- it’s like dirty mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.’
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer – the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates – and his daughter rebekah.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
“i knew that a 'job' no matter how high up i was, was only going to limit my potentials and i was only helping my boss get rich, but not help anyone else through that process. even in a traditional business, i had to depend on staff, market and many other factors. the only thing we all have in common is the 24 hrs of the day. no one has more or less of that 24 hrs. but, many of us unfortunately, trade time for money and have absolutely no time for anything else but work. i realized what mattered is how we spend it. work smarter why harder. i wanted to build something strong in a shorter period of time by being smarter about it and create our own economy, be in control of it and so decided to take the action of starting a business with a different approach and vision.” @miss.grace.chung ✨
——————————————————

text:
justice for lai dai han gives a voice to the victims and their children and is campaigning for a formal @unitednationshumanrights investigation into the allegations of widespread sexual violence by south korean troops.

our work seeks to raise public awareness, to allow political and community leaders to connect with the victims of sexual violence to understand their suffering first hand, and to create public art as a permanent reminder of the plight of the ldh.

money raised through fundraising efforts in 2019, will support the campaign and the victims and their children, many of which live in poor rural communities and suffer from low levels of literacy and poor access to education, healthcare and other social services. .

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
🔥 новые слоганы, платформы и штаб-квартиры: чем удивили нас корпорации на прошедшей неделе?
⠀
🇷🇺 вконтакте объявил, что в 2019 году в крупных городах россии появятся официальные представители соцсети. они будут анализировать особенности потребления медиа и создания контента в конкретном регионе. первый этап проекта стартует 30 января в екатеринбурге.
⠀
👨 gillette выпустил рекламный ролик «мы верим», в котором в рамках движения #metoo призвал мужчин изменить своё поведение и остановить насилие, домогательства и травлю. компания отказалась от слогана «лучше для мужчины нет» («the best man can get»), который использовала более 30 лет подряд. новый слоган gillette — «лучший мужчина, который может быть» («the best men can be»).
⠀
💙 компания pepsi также впервые за семь лет сменила слоган. теперь это «for the love of it» — «всё ради любви». с 2012 года слоган компании звучал так: «live for now» — «живи здесь и сейчас». кроме того, пепси также представила новый дизайн своих банок и бутылок.
⠀
📝 wordpress, google, automattic, spirited media и news revenue hub анонсировали newspack — cms для медиа с ориентацией на небольшие сми. newspack — это новая платформа с открытым исходным кодом для новостных проектов. в ней разработчики планируют реализовать лучшие редакционные и бизнес-практики в цифровом издательстве.
⠀
🕊 твиттер запустит бета-программу для тестирования новых функций, среди которых цветные ответы и статусы. соцсеть будет анализировать использование новых опций перед внедрением в основную пользовательскую базу.
⠀
🥇 яндекс отметит организации с высоким рейтингом специальным значком «хорошее место». значок получат организации всех типов — от отелей и баров до рекламных агентств.
⠀
⛔️ youtube запретил публиковать видео с участием в опасных челленджах. кроме того, в силу вступил запрет на пранки и ролики с розыгрышами, просмотр которых может вызвать стресс у пользователей сети.
⠀

16 days 16 films 
have a keek at the trailer 
totally am honoured to have worked with these guys and would def recommend and work with them again 💖

our winning films were: 🥉3. silence - fiona compton 🥈2. everybody’s business - miranda stern
🥇1. circle - jayisha

#16days16films #whatcanido #jointheconversation 
told through a fictional protagonist's vlog, this film explores gender-based violence in the workplace - something which 1 in 3 women experience, but only 22% of whom ever report. 'if we want things to change then this really has to become ‘everybody’s business’.' the end of the film poses a very direct challenge: transformation must include men if change is going to happen.

text:
diese petition gegen r.kelly 
zeigt sehr gutwie doppelmoral, rassistische stereotype funktionieren und wie die opfer mal wieder in den hintergrund geraten.ich versteh garnicht,was diese gekünstelte empörungswelle die sich derzeit ausschließlich an r.kelly richtet bezwecken soll. wie gesagt ich unterstüzte ihn nicht,dass er schwarze minderjährige und frauen sexuell missbraucht hat wissen wir seit jahrzenten und ja er gehört in's gefängnis. genau so wie donald trump,wody allen,kevin spacey,jeremy pievens,ben afflec und alle anderen sexualstraftäter.und auch hier ist ganz offensichtlich,dass r.kelly im gegensatz zu allen anderen weißen abgebrühten mistkerlen öffentlich gelnyched wird,weil er schwarz ist.
das rassistische system in amerika juckt es nicht,dass schwarze frauen und kinder vergewaltigt werden.
wenn es weiße frauen und kinder wären,hätte die sache ganz anders ausgesehen. amerikas geschichte basiert übrigens auf mord,sklaverei,ausbeutung und  sexuellen missbrauch und vergewaltigung seitens weißer männer und frauen.das haben die jahrhundertelang gemacht und wurden
im vergleich zu anderen straftätern die margnalisiert sind, nie oder sehr mild dafür bestraft und heute ist es immer noch so.
#harvey weinstein,der von unzähligen frauen unter dem hashtag #metoo,sexueller missbrauch vorgeworfen wurde,läuft einfach frei rum und wird medial nicht so ausseinander genommen. das ist für mich heuchlerische doppelmoral und deswegen werde ich die petition gegen r.kelly nicht unterschreiben,solange dasselbe nicht auch mit allen anderen sexualstrafttätern unabhängig von ihrer hautfarbe ,sozialen status und privilegien passiert!
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

.
.

.
.

#your#activism#is#shit
#white#men#are#sexual
#predators#and#phedophile
#its#not#about#rkelly#
#but#the#racist#system
#which#doesnt#protect
#black#women#and#girls

mensaje importante
hola a todas, veréis hoy un periodista nos preguntaba lo siguiente:
¿cómo se os ocurrió montar esta iniciativa? 
pues la respuesta que le vamos a dar es clara, por que en pleno s.xxi año 2019, seguimos recibiendo estos mensajes, una de nuestras hermanas (la cual como nos ha pedido vamos a preservar au anonimato) nos ha enviado este email qué veis en la foto. a ti hermana te decimos lo siguiente: 
1. que no tengas miedo, que eres libres
2. que vamos a seguir peleando por nuestra marca para ayudar a todas las mujeres que nos necesiten
3. que jamás vuelvas a tener ningún tipo de contacto con tu marido 
y por último a todas nuestras seguidoras de instagram esto no puede seguir pasando, por favor compartir esta imagen (haciendo una captura de pantalla) con el hastag #estaesnuestramanada y etiquetando a nuestra cuenta la difusión es fundamental

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

text:
a close shave? (just couldn’t stand by, so #metoo)
shaving company gillette has recently launched its new controversial ad campaign which immediately became extensively lauded along with getting severe backlash. among the objections there are claims that the commercial teaches boys to be cowards and pussies, alleging that there is nothing morally wrong about catcalling, or portrays most men as dangerous perpetrators, harassers and bullies forcing them to feel ashamed of their masculinity. it even comes down to the arguments that males are just helpless victims of demonic and vicious femininity. 
let’s just do a simple exercise. think for a moment and list the things a woman should do not to get raped.
.
.
take your time.
.
. 
i’m sure in about five minutes you can come up with the list of at least ten bullet points, among which you will definitely find something like not wearing revealing clothes, not walking alone at night, not drinking too much alcohol at parties, not walking into lifts with strangers and the list can go on. .
.
now think what a man should do not to get raped.
.
.
share your ideas, if you like. i’ve got only one.
.
. 
exploring social dynamics and hierarchy boys learn to man up, to suck it up and brush it off. boys don’t cry. boys will be boys. or will they? the thing is that being a man comes with extra measure of power and the question comes up what to do with that power, either to be violent and sexist, policing each other not to be girlish, or to stand up for somebody who has less power, to be compassionate, to be respectful towards other people’s feelings and desires (or their absence). #gillette #gillettead #gillettecommercial #masculinity #metoo #notaskingforit #blue #staircase

text:
ce week-end, des dizaines de milliers de personnes se sont mobilisées aux etats-unis, mais aussi au royaume-uni et en france pour la défense des droits des femmes avec la #womensmarch.

ce mouvement né le 21 janvier 2017, il y a 2 ans jour pour jour, suite à l’élection de #donaldtrump, connaît plusieurs vagues de protestations.

l’année dernière, le très conservateur #brettkavanaugh, accédait au prestigieux titre de juge à la cour suprême. cette nomination suscite l’indignation, et pour cause, cet homme est accusé de tentative de viol… le mouvement féministe reprend de l’ampleur et une nouvelle manifestation s’organise dans les rues nord-américaines.

cette année, la « vague rose » repart sous de meilleurs auspices puisqu'une élection est à marquer d’une pierre blanche : les femmes ont pris place dans la sphère politique américaine grâce à un record historique… 127 femmes ont été élues aux dernières élections de mi-mandat, nombre jamais égalé jusqu’à présent.

#alexandriaocasiocortez, la plus jeune femme élue au congrès américain a d’ailleurs participé à la marche de new york où elle s’est exprimée devant la foule : « nous ne laisserons personne nous enlever nos droits, en fait nous en aurons davantage » a-t-elle déclaré en promettant un projet de loi sur l’égalité hommes-femmes.

de plus, la sénatrice démocrate #kirstengillibrand, pilier du mouvement #metoo, s’est lancée dans la course à la présidentielle.

you go girls ! .
📷 : @clemence_gouy pour #wondher / @womensmarch (washington) / @ah_thenah (san francisco) / @womensmarchlondon (londres) / @cindyglucas (paris) / @ocasio2018 (new york)
.
#wondher #cejourlà #womensmarch #womensmarch2019 #womensmarchnyc #womensmarchwashington #womensmarchsanfrancisco #womensmarchlondon #womensmarchparis #womensmarch2017 #illustration #womensrights #march #manifestation #fightforyourrights #égalité #empowerment #womenempowerment

text: paradoxen att vi bara borde finnas på ett sätt som gör det omöjligt att kännas vid oss! om vi höjer våra röster, höjer ni era ögonbryn och ifrågasätter oss. när vi delar med oss av vår vardag och vittnar om övergrepp vi är med om menar ni att vi inte kan ha det så dåligt, om vi ändå finns på instagram. stereotyper om hur en missbrukare eller prostituerad ska se ut och bete sig skapar fördomar om utsatthet och vem som är utsatt på ”rätt sätt” och inte. det blir ofta diskussion om ansvar och val, där utomstående ifrågasätter varför vi inte gör mer och varför vi inte väljer på alla dom många olika ”lösningar” som finns. vi har psykvård, vi har socialtjänst, vi har polis, det finns jobb som inte kräver utbildning, ingen behöver vara hemlös, det finns missbruksvård osv. ingen ramlar mellan stolarna, ingen behöver va utsatt. så är det inte. och om vi var utsatta på ”rätt” sätt, dvs så utsatta som det krävs för att tas på allvar, så hade våra röster aldrig hörts. vilket är precis vad samhället vill - att vi ska hålla käften om vi inte är så utsatta att vi inte har tillgång till vår egen röst. så att vi förblir osynliga och ohörda. #intedinhora #metoo #prostitution #missbruk

text:
そう、私は北陵小学校と
いうところ出身だ。
なぜか昼休みくらいの
掃除時間は基本的に
なぜかだいたい
トイレの清掃に
割り当てられていた
小学校４年生の時
５年生には姉の幼なじみの
日高美貴ちゃん
６年生にはいまや女優の
松下奈緒ちゃん
その時、彼女達は一切掃除をせずに
入り口で私を見下していただけ

そしてこの女優になった
松下奈緒ちゃん
やっぱり私の歌詞を使っている
あ、奈緒ちゃん...
加害者側だったんだ...
とようやく気づいた

text:
"let us not seek to satisfy our thirst for freedom by drinking from the cup of bitterness and hatred." - martin luther king, jr. 1963 "i have a dream" speech.
⠀⠀
i hadn't read this speech in a very long time.  the powerful and timeless words of dr. king's 1963 speech were written in the context of racial equality, an issue that still plagues our nation.  i won't disrespect his life's work by pretending that his words were intended for anything other than his fight for racial equality. ⠀⠀
when we think of this speech, we most often think of the part where dr. king describes his dream.  the quote above, however, really jumped out at me this time.  again, not pretending that these words had anything to do with me, a middle-class white woman, but i find that they could be applicable to all of those who experience oppression or injustice.  in the midst of #metoo, #neveragain, and #loveislove just to name a few, i interpret these words to mean that we cannot fall victim to hate while we fight our respective battles.  in other words, 'an eye for an eye leaves the whole world blind'. ⠀⠀
as the owner of midland moms blog (and i realize this is a far reach from racial equality), i am reminded every day how important mothers are to one another.  we cannot turn against each other or fall victim to gossip or judgment.  despite our differences as individuals, we have one thing in common: we are moms and we owe it ourselves and each other to lift each other up; to celebrate each other. ⠀⠀
if it's been a while since you've read the speech, take a few minutes to read it again. find the words that speak to you.  more importantly, and i cannot stress this enough, understand that this speech speaks someone else, too.  we are all fighting battles, some big, some small.  when you understand that everyone is fighting for something, perhaps we can begin to cut each other a little slack.
⠀⠀ .
.
.

text:
rapper yo-yo recalls an inappropriate encounter with r. kelly. 
saturday night (january 19th), tmz caught up with veteran emcee yo-yo as she entered the trumpet awards at the cobb energy performing arts center in atlanta. naturally, the outlet brought up the topic of r. kelly and the controversy surrounding the newly-minted surviving r. kelly documentary series.

when prompted, yo-yo revealed that she frequently visited r. kelly at his los angeles studio and that in one instance she brought along her daughter who would later tell her mother that one of the members of r. kelly’s camp put the singer’s number in her phone. “i actually went to listen to his music and my daughter came with me,” she tells the outlet in the clip. “the sad part was when we got home, my daughter said, ‘mom, someone passed me r. kelly’s number. i said, ‘what!?’ she’s like, ‘mom, please don’t say nothing. this is why i didn’t tell you.’ “i didn’t say anything, but you know, it really let me know there is a real problem,” she continues. “it really let me know that there really is a problem because with all of that that was going on for that to still happen — and it happened to me. i was thinking i’m your friend. i come here with my daughter who’s over 21, but you don’t know my daughter’s age, and behind my back? you will slide my daughter your number? that’s just weird to me, like a weirdo. who would do that?” yo-yo went on to add that she did not fully recognize the seriousness of the issue at hand until it involved her child, adding that she fully sympathizes with r. kelly’s alleged victims. peep the video in the full story at www.itskenbarbie.com (or swipe)what do you guys think? #rkelly #robertkelly #survivingrkelly #lifetimetv #trappedinthecloset #muterkelly #metoo #yoyo #youcantplaywithmyyoyo #femalerapper #femalerappers #entertainment #entertainmentnews #entertainmentblog #gossip

text:
why rwanda?

rwanda is the host country of 2019 awlc

in recognition of its gender development strides, awlo has chosen rwanda as this year's host of african women in leadership conference. we are committed to driving change through partnerships for sustainable development, and have identified shared values with rwanda.

we are proud of a heforshe champion @paulkagame whose administration has not brought women closer to leadership but also facilitated structures for sustainability of his impact. 
these progressive values are aligned with ours, and we are beaming the light on country's development through african women in leadership conference.

earlybird registration is still on via awlo.org/awlc/rwanda2019

who should attend?

expected delegates are women organizations, professionals, entrepreneurs, public service, civil society organizations, philanthropists, youths, head of government agencies, first ladies, politicians, diplomates and other stakeholders. @rwandaeventsgroup @unwomen @unitednations @jewelhowardtaylor @flyrwandair

#rwandaevents #womenforwomen #womenofworth #ugandawomen #southafricawomen
#bosslady #diversity #metoo #womeninleadership #womenwhowork #workingclasswomen #girlboss #bossbabe #celebratingwomen #femalefounders #inspirewomen #femaleentrepreneur #womenempowerment #diaspora #inspire #boss #manager #africa #womenofafrica #genderparity #awlo

text:
deep breath—here it goes. 
3 1/2 years ago, i began to recover memory of nearly 24 years of abuse at the hands of a trusted relative. i cannot begin to describe the damage caused by this degree of trauma to me as a child, teen and young-adult—so i won’t.  instead, i share my post-traumatic growth as recorded in my sketchbooks. 
this is my superpower—using art to process and contain big scary concepts. 
no shocking images—trigger warnings not necessary. instead, i hope to share a little awareness, empathy and humor with those who have sadly been through something similar or love someone who has.

text: the body really does keep the score. mine did. it was the price i paid in exchange for forty-seven  years of anesthesized ignorance. ignorance (in no way blissful) of trauma buried deep below consciousness in my survivor brain. after years of treatment-resistant depression (thankfully gone now), it began to spill into my body. the first year i got sick, i saw 12 doctors hoping to figure out what was going on. i radically changed my lifestyle and diet trying to regain my health, but nothing helped. my physical health improved only after i was forced to face and release my “new” past. i keep telling myself that being present, despite the paralyzing flashbacks and my pal perma-shame, is worth the recovery of my physical health. numbing out just kicks recovery farther down the road.

text: i drew this in frustration over 10 years ago to show the twelfth doctor i had seen that year. i had grown weary (pun intended) of trying to communicate how very exhausted i was.  i had found that saying “i’m just so tired” was an invitation to be dismissed by most medical professionals (the first doctor i saw told me “it’s probably just fibromyalgia—which is basically depression”). this drawing (plus a doctor who knew how to listen) validated my experience—and is one of the reasons i love the expressive quality of art.

text: one of the most difficult things about recovering memories of my childhood was the realization that the world as i thought i knew it was no longer a safe place. even worse was the fact that the thief of my innocence was a goofy and kind uncle—someone who had been a consistent presence in my large and closely knit extended family. my worldview completely shifted in a sad and sickening way. i doubt i’ll ever make peace with this sad fact, but i am working on accepting it (with all its accompanying discomfort and grief). for me, this has meant allowing for gray tones in a previously black and white moral construct.

text:
therapy is fun. 
actually it’s not. it’s work and it’s exhausting. the mental energy required to process and contain memories of this nature is all-consuming and leaves me shaking for days after each weekly session. i am not complaining—emdr is a miracle and my therapist is a miracle worker.  i can’t imagine trusting anybody else with the hopeless mess between my ears. she is smart, wise, patient, fearless  and insightful. her instincts are scary-accurate. she is a safe constant in this baffling phase (please, please let this just be a phase) of my life. it took me 3 weeks of frantic therapist shopping to find her during that initial bleeding-out phase of memory recovery. best decision i could have made.

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
82年生まれ、キム・ジヨン

女性への困難、差別。全くもって韓国だけの話じゃない。悲しいけれど、日本でも起きている。これを真剣に考えて変えようとしている人はどのくらいいるだろうか。私はこの現状を諦めたくない。大衆の意見を変えるって難しいことだけれど、この#metoo 現象でみんなの意識が少しでも変わったら嬉しい。

衝撃だったのは韓国で妊娠中の子供が女児だと分かると中絶する人もいて、男女比率が均等じゃなかった年があるということ。涙が溢れました。日本人古い考えを持ったままのの男性がこれを聞いたらどう思うのかな。自分のやっていることは棚に上げて、そんなのひどいなんていうのかな。

嵐の大野くんが、パワハラとかセクハラとか言われて生きにくくなった(ニュアンス違うかも？)といったことを雑誌で言ってて、唖然としました。ようやく苦しんでいる人が声をあげられる世の中に変わりつつあるのに。影響力のある人がそんなこと言わないで。。。変わることはポジティブなことだと思うし、私自身もどんどん、いい方向へ変わっていきたい。
帯の女性たちの絶望が詰まったこの本は、未来に向かうための希望の書というフレーズにぐっときた。#82년생김지영 #読書  #82年生まれキムジヨン #勉強垢

自分メモ
•韓国では外国語や科学に特化した高校など特別な学校を除いて高校受験がなく、地元の高校に割り当てられる。

text:
footage of nigel farage swigging a pint and thanking steve bannon and breitbart for the brexit result was deleted from a breitbart youtube channel, following the data scandal surrounding cambridge analytica.
.
- well done bannon, well done breitbart, the ex-ukip leader announces in the short clip. - you helped with this. hugely.

farage’s nod to steve bannon certainly hasn’t aged well in the context of the recent storm around cambridge analytica’s influence over the eu referendum.

it was revealed that data from 50 million facebook profiles were looked at against the electoral register, and then used to build an algorithm which analyses people’s personality traits in relation to their voting behaviour.

this data could then be used to find potential swing voters and create messages tailored to influence them politically.

the firm’s vice president at the time was steve bannon, who was also head of the right-wing website breitbart and was running donald trump’s campaign to become us president.

anna o'donohue
inews

text:
what does real leadership look like in the #metoo era?
#
we are caught in a circular conversation about why there aren’t more women in leadership. we bemoan the fact that there are only 24 women ceos in the fortune 500, that senior manager-level men outnumber women two to one, and that in the c-suite, just 23% are women. and the media continue to joke, pointing out that in top leadership ranks there are fewer women than people called john. yet we still use the same approaches to identify, hire and promote leaders that produce the same lacklustre results: disengaged employees who don’t trust their bosses and an inability to select and develop the right leaders for the future. and all this in middle of the #metoo era. as the world leaders prepare for the world economic forum's annual meeting in davos, leaders (the majority of them men) should be asking what lessons can we learn from recent case studies in leadership malfunction, and how we can fine-tune our selection criteria to not only make our leaders more diverse, but also elevate their general quality. less than 25% of women hold senior leadership roles organizations interested in getting more diverse leaders and better results can start with the following three steps:…

text:
being in the philippines has been a stark reminder of all the dualities in my life... contradicting, contrasting and clashing. i've spent most of my life shying away from them for fear of the conflicts they've caused; especially within myself. .
.
it wasn't until recently that i finally learned to appreciate the breathe + depth of perspective & experiences those dualities have afforded me, and in turn be comfortable, confident, and proud of the person i've become as a result of them. .
.
i've come to understand that moving forward involves a lot of looking back, and i'm grateful for the blessing to be doing just that. 🇵🇭

text:
📸📸📸
from @cheerstohappyhour (recipe below)
.
new cocktail bar alert!! last tuesday, @projectgigglewater opened its doors to the public for the first time (second time if you include nye!) and the drinks are a knockout punch to the kisser. it’s great to see more attention-to-detail driven cocktail spots opening up in the dundas west neighbourhood - making it a total destination for artisanal drink enthusiasts.
.
here’s a tall, berrylicious refresher with a hint of smoke and a delicious bite. it’s a bit lower in abv and i had it with olives all’ascolana and curried cauliflower popcorn.
.
drink: el finablo
0.5 oz @mezcalaguasanta mezcal
1.5 oz fino sherry
0.5 oz cassis
0.5 oz lime
ginger beer
.
method:
shake with ice and strain into a collins glass. garnish: mint and dehydrated lime.

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
for anyone unsure about rape culture (which is not all about just penetration) and whether it's "real" then this is a great article.  well done to the women of thailand for trying to change culture.

wongsawang experienced an attempted rape when she was 20 by a friend while at university. “at that time i didn’t understand what had happened to me,” she says. “so for a year i kept quiet, with this eating away at my heart.” but over the course of a year, the same thing happened to eight of her friends, who were all raped, harassed or sexually assaulted by people they knew but had no idea how to handle it or who to go to. those who did report it were rarely taken seriously. “i kept thinking: was this normal in our society?” says wongsawang. “especially as our attackers would go on as normal, as if nothing wrong had happened.” https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/jan/17/time-to-start-talking-about-consent-thailands-nascent-metoo-moment

if you've followed my career any then you've encountered jane(@surrija) one of my most trusted, and most respected collaborators and friends, from dr. horrible's sing along blog -live!- in san diego, to the workshop of pretendo: a musical 5 years ago, and the reading of she kills monsters for @artistsatplayla a few years back, and most recently #vietgone at @eastwestplayers! now shes about to head off to @osfashland for another run of @cambodianrockband!

shes also in the final weeks of her #kickstarter for her 4th studio album!  i've been privileged  to hear some of the early cuts as shes been developing this... theres some powerful stuff here!

a theme of this album is inspired by the lovers of #pablopicasso, and some of the songs are written in their voices... were they his muses? or were they the art itself... as he manipulated,  and burned through these women, was the value in the work he generated because of them? or was the value in the lives they lived in spite of him?  thematically  this work echoes where we are now as a culture... #womensmarch, post #metoo, #femcongress and this need to take back narratives, and reevaluate things, people and ideologies we have revered, or just complacently accepted... without question.

please help make this album happen! shes $7k away!

reposted from @surrija - (1/5) sound. kickstarter link in profile.
short: barcelona (rough mix)
long: it’s a dot on the map and also my way back into what feels like home in music. written to the painting le rêve, though i’m probably in the words somewhere since full escapes are never really possible.

it’s indescribable to look back at years of incrementals and see evolution with hindsight. i am drop dead lucky to have such generous minds to travel with and am so proud of this thing we made.

visit kickstarter and put me to work!! to my pledgers, words can’t express how grateful i am that you are aboard.
with love, 
j

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day.

michelle nichols
reuters
